The '''W.E.B. Du Bois Career of Distinguished Scholarship Award''' is given annually by the [[American Sociological Association]] to a scholar among its members whose cumulative body of work constitutes a significant contribution to the advancement of [[sociology]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.asanet.org/news-events/member-awards/web-dubois-career-award|title=W.E.B. Du Bois Career of Distinguished Scholarship Award|date=2016-04-22|work=American Sociological Association|access-date=2017-11-07|language=en}}</ref>. Formerly called simply the '''Career of Distinguished Scholarship Award''', the award was renamed in 2006 to honor pioneering American sociologist [[W. E. B. Du Bois]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.asanet.org/sites/default/files/savvy/footnotes/mayjun06/indexthree.html|title=Members Propose Resolution to Rename ASA Awards|website=www.asanet.org|access-date=2017-11-07}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.asanet.org/sites/default/files/savvy/footnotes/mayjun06/fn12.html|title=Background on Proposed Name Change for ASA’s Distinguished Scholarship Award|website=www.asanet.org|access-date=2017-11-07}}</ref>.
